<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n42054a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n42" href="#n42054a">N42 (VI.B.31)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n42all.htm#n42054a"> 54(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Es-Safa-Marwah</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">a strange sight &hellip; presented itself in the vale of Mekka &hellip; The ancient city is for three days evacuated by all its inhabitants &hellip; and as they retire, the exiled converts &hellip; revisit the empty homes of their childhood and &hellip; fulfil the rites of pilgrimage &hellip; as with the Prophet at their head they make the circuit of the Kaaba and the rapid procession <mark>between Es-Saf&#257; and Marwah</mark> <small> Stanley Lane-Poole, <a name="SLPS" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#SLPS"><cite title="source">The Speeches and Table-Talk of the Prophet Mohammad</cite></a> (1882) xlv-xlvi</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
